                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The Hay Wain is an oil painting regarded as one of the greatest English landscape masterpieces. It depicts a rural scene on the River Stour between the English counties of Suffolk and Essex, showing a large cart (or wain) crossing the shallow river. The painting reflects Constable's deep love for the Suffolk countryside and his revolutionary approach to depicting natural light and atmosphere.",
